							<h4>Shutting Down the Monitor</h4>
							<br />
							<p>With a laptop computer, when you power off and shut down the computer, everything turns off. With a desktop computer, when you power off and shut it down, you are turning off the computer, but not the monitor. The monitor is where the screen is located and it must be powered off and shut down separately.</p>
							
							<p>Most monitors will have small buttons somewhere along the frame of the screen. The on/off button for your monitor will look something like these pictures below:</p>
							<hr>
							</div>
						</div>	
							

						<div class="row">
							<div class="twelve columns">								
							<h4>On/Off Button on Computer Monitor</h4>
							<br />
							<img class="left space" src="images/computerbasics/MonitorOnOff.jpg" alt="">														
							<p>It is best to shut the monitor off <strong>after</strong> you have powered off and shut down the computer. This is because if there are any problems with shutting down the computer, any error messages or other information will be on the screen. If the screen is already off, you won't be able to see them.</p>
							<p>The same goes for powering up your computer. Make sure you turn on the monitor first, so if there are any problems with starting the computer, any error messages or other information will be on the screen. If the screen is still off, you won't be able to see them.</p>
							
							<p>Once the computer is completly powered off and shut down, press the on/off button on the monitor. You will know that it is off when the green light on the monitor goes off.</p>
